-- Venezuela Shuts Down 89 McDonald’s Restaurants Over Tax Records
-- B y   N a t h a n   C r o o k s
-- 2012-07-31T22:54:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-31/venezuela-shuts-down-89-mcdonald-s-restaurants-over-tax-records.html
Venezuela ’s national tax authority
Seniat today ordered a three-day shutdown of 89 McDonald’s
restaurants across the country on the grounds of inadequate
bookkeeping, the agency said in an e-mailed statement without
providing additional information.  The closed McDonald’s franchises are operated by Cia.
Operativa de Alimentos COR CA, Caracas-based El Mundo newspaper
 reported  today on its website. Another 51 McDonald’s restaurants
in Venezuela were not affected because they are operated by
other franchises, the Caracas-based newspaper reported.  For Related News and Information:  To contact the reporter on this story:
